feat(phase-1c): JAD Docker Compose stack + OpenAPI client setup

Phase 1c Docker Compose Development Profile for the full JAD stack:

Infrastructure (docker-compose.jad.yml):
- 16 services: Traefik v3.4, PostgreSQL 17, Vault, Keycloak, NATS,
  EDC-V Control/Data Planes, IdentityHub, IssuerService, CFM Agents
- Traefik Docker provider with *.localhost routing
- Full health check dependency ordering
- Multi-database PostgreSQL init (7 databases)
- Vault bootstrap (JWT auth, Keycloak JWKS, policies)
- Keycloak realm import (edcv realm, roles, OAuth2 clients)

Configuration (jad/): 13 config files
OpenAPI (jad/openapi/): 5 specs from JAD repo
TypeScript Client (ui/src/lib/edc/): type-safe API client with OAuth2
Scripts: bootstrap-jad.sh + generate-api-types.sh

Refs: https://github.com/Metaform/jad
